PSSM Creation and Visualisation

require(Biostrings)
require(ggseqlogo)
require(ggplot2)

statData <- read.csv('~/Downloads/Final Project/Datasets/StatData.csv')

#Subset Sequences for labelled data
sequencesAKT <- statData[statData$Label == 'AKT', 5]
sequencesMTOR <- statData[statData$Label == 'mTOR', 5]

#Build PSSM for both labelled AKT and mTOR data
string_set.AKT <- AAStringSet(sequencesAKT)
PSSM.AKT <- round(consensusMatrix(string_set.AKT, as.prob = T), 5)
string_set.mTOR <- AAStringSet(sequencesMTOR)
PSSM.mTOR <- round(consensusMatrix(string_set.mTOR, as.prob = T), 5)


#Create a new column for PSSM Score AKT and mTOR
statData$PSSM_SCORE_AKT = 0
statData$PSSM_SCORE_mTOR = 0

#For each row in the data assign a PSSM score based on AKT.
for (i in 1:nrow(statData)) {
  #Set score to be 0
  score <- 0
  #Get the sequence to be testest and convert to a list of amino acids
  exampleSequence <- toString(statData[i, 5])
  exampleSequence <- list(strsplit(exampleSequence, ""))
  exampleSequence <- exampleSequence[[1]][[1]]
  #For each amino acid, sum its PSSM score
  for (j in 1:length(exampleSequence)) {
    if (exampleSequence[j] == "_") {
      next
    }
    score <- score + PSSM.AKT[exampleSequence[j], j][[1]]
  }
  statData[i , 31] = score
}

#mTOR PSSM Score
for (i in 1:nrow(statData)) {
  #Set score to be 0
  score <- 0
  #Get the sequence to be testest and convert to a list of amino acids
  exampleSequence <- toString(statData[i, 5])
  exampleSequence <- list(strsplit(exampleSequence, ""))
  exampleSequence <- exampleSequence[[1]][[1]]
  #For each amino acid, sum its PSSM score
  for (j in 1:13) {
    if (exampleSequence[j] == "_") {
      next
    }
    score <- score + PSSM.mTOR[exampleSequence[j], j][[1]]
  }
  statData[i, 32] = score
}

Create two models using positive unlabelled ensemble learning (Pengyi, 2016):

Idea is to set either AKTOR or MTOR as positive and a random sample of unlabelled data as negative and then train a model on it. We then evaluate the confidence (c) of the model. This is the probability of the model predicting a positive when the label is actually positive on the training data (i.e. train on data and then predict back on data).

We then create base classifiers using the same data and use it to predict on the total dataset and generate probabilities for positive vs. negative. The positive probability for each row is then divided by the models’s confidence value. For example, if there is 50 ensembles created then there will be 50 different positive probabilities for each row and each probability is divided by the model’s confidence. For each row this resulting value is divided by the total ensemble number. The final probabilities are found by dividing this last number by the max value of that group of numbers.

Create a function that returns the prediction results given a substrate, ensemble size, specific model, and kernel type.

prediction <- function(trainData, substrateName, cmodel, ensembleSize, kernelType, predict.mat, polynomial = FALSE) {

  substrateData = trainData[trainData$label == substrateName,]
  notSubstrateData = trainData[trainData$label != substrateName,]
  
  #sampling from the negative data
  models <- list()
  estimated_c <- c()
  tot.acc <- c()
  
  ##Can change ensemblesize to any number based on desired number of ensembles to make
  for (r in 1:ensembleSize){
      set.seed(r)
      id <- sample(1:nrow(notSubstrateData), size = length(substrateData), replace = F)
      negative.samples <- rownames(notSubstrateData)[id]
      negative.train <- trainData[negative.samples, ]
  
      # classification
      x <- rbind(substrateData, negative.train)
      x <- x[,-1]
      rownames(x) <- NULL
      
      # estimating confidence
      if (cmodel == 'svm') {
      cls <- as.factor(rep(c(1, 2), times=c(nrow(substrateData), length(substrateData))))
      k <- 3
      fold <- createFolds(cls, k)
      svm_model <- svm(x[-fold$Fold1,], cls[-fold$Fold1], kernel=kernelType, probability=T, scale = F, degree = polynomial)
  
      # label 1 correspond to positive labelled examples
      p <- which(cls[fold$Fold1] == 1)
      pred <- predict(svm_model, x[fold$Fold1,][p,], decision.values=F, probability=T);
      estimated.c <- sum(attr(pred, "probabilities")[,1]) / nrow(attr(pred, "probabilities"))
      estimated_c <- c(estimated_c, estimated.c)
      
      # training base classifiers
      models[[r]] <- svm(x, cls, kernel=kernelType, probability=T, scale = F, degree = polynomial)
      }
  
      else {
      cls <- as.factor(rep(c("P", "N"), times=c(nrow(substrateData), length(substrateData))))
      k <- 3
      fold <- createFolds(cls, k)
      trnCtrl=trainControl(method='cv', number=1, returnResamp='none', summaryFunction = twoClassSummary, classProbs = TRUE)
      model=train(x[-fold$Fold1,], cls[-fold$Fold1], method=cmodel, trControl=trnCtrl,  metric = "ROC")
      
        # label p correspond to positive labelled examples
      p <- which(cls[fold$Fold1] == 'P')
        pred <- predict(object=model, x[fold$Fold1,][p,], type='prob')
        estimated.c <- sum(pred[,2]) / nrow(pred)
        estimated_c <- c(estimated_c, estimated.c)
      
    # training base classifiers
      models[[r]] <- train(x, cls, method=cmodel, trControl=trnCtrl,  metric = "ROC")  
        
      } 
    }
  
    ensemble.pred.corrected.100 <- 0
    ensemble.pred.corrected.250 <- 0
    ensemble.pred.corrected.500 <- 0
    ensemble.pred.corrected.750 <- 0
    ensemble.pred.corrected.1000 <- 0
    if (cmodel == 'svm') {
    for(i in 1:length(models)) {
        mod.pred <- predict(models[[i]], predict.mat, decision.values=TRUE, probability=TRUE)
        if (i <= 100) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.100 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.100 + attr(mod.pred,"probabilities")[,1] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        if (i <= 250) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.250 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.250 + attr(mod.pred,"probabilities")[,1] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        if (i <= 500) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.500 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.500 + attr(mod.pred,"probabilities")[,1] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        if (i <= 750) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.750 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.750 + attr(mod.pred,"probabilities")[,1] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        ensemble.pred.corrected.1000 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.1000 + attr(mod.pred,"probabilities")[,1] / estimated_c[i]
    }
    }
    else {
    for(i in 1:length(models)) {
        mod.pred <- predict(models[[i]], predict.mat, type = 'prob')
        if (i <= 100) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.100 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.100 + mod.pred[,2] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        if (i <= 250) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.250 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.250 + mod.pred[,2] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        if (i <= 500) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.500 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.500 + mod.pred[,2] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        if (i <= 750) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.750 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.750 + mod.pred[,2] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        ensemble.pred.corrected.1000 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.1000 + mod.pred[,2] / estimated_c[i]
    }  
    }
    
    results <- list()
    predicts.100 <- (ensemble.pred.corrected.100 / 100)
    results$prediction_100 <- predicts.100/max(predicts.100)
    predicts.250 <- (ensemble.pred.corrected.250 / 250)
    results$prediction_250 <- predicts.250/max(predicts.250)
    predicts.500 <- (ensemble.pred.corrected.500 / 500)
    results$prediction_500 <- predicts.500/max(predicts.500)
    predicts.750 <- (ensemble.pred.corrected.750 / 750)
    results$prediction_750 <- predicts.750/max(predicts.750)
    predicts.1000 <- (ensemble.pred.corrected.1000 / 1000)
    results$prediction_1000 <- predicts.1000/max(predicts.1000)
    
    results$models <- models
  predictions = data.frame(results$prediction_100,results$prediction_250, results$prediction_500, results$prediction_750,     results$prediction_1000)
    
    return(predictions)
  
}

Create a function which compares predictions vs benchmark and returns the absolute difference in prediciton confidence

require(readxl)
require(sqldf)

setwd('~/Downloads/Final project/')
pengYi <- read_xlsx('prediction_2016.xlsx')
pengYi_mTOR <- read_xlsx('prediction_2016.xlsx', sheet = 2)

#Rename Columns to use in SQL
colnames(pengYi)[c(2,3,6)] <- c('phosphorylation_site','sequence_window', 'full_model_predict')
colnames(pengYi_mTOR)[c(2,3,6)] <- c('phosphorylation_site','sequence_window', 'full_model_predict')

accuracy <- function(predictions, totalData, benchmark)  {

  #Join the prediction columns
  data = cbind(totalData, predictions)
  
  #Rename Columns to use in SQL
  colnames(data)[c(6, 34:38)] <- c('seq_window', 'prediction_100', 'prediction_250', 'prediction_500', 'prediction_750', 'prediction_1000')
  
  #Join PenYi's Predictions to create a Resisual Error
  joinedData <- sqldf('SELECT d.Identifier, d.GeneSymbol, d.PhosphorylationSite, d.seq_window, p.GeneSymbol, p.phosphorylation_site, p.sequence_window, p.full_model_predict, d.prediction_100, d.prediction_250, d.prediction_500, d.prediction_750, d.prediction_1000 FROM data d JOIN benchmark p ON (d.seq_window = p.sequence_window AND d.PhosphorylationSite = p.phosphorylation_site)')
  
  joinedData$AbsoluteDifference.100 = abs(joinedData$prediction_100 - joinedData$full_model_predict)
  joinedData$AbsoluteDifference.250 = abs(joinedData$prediction_250 - joinedData$full_model_predict)
  joinedData$AbsoluteDifference.500 = abs(joinedData$prediction_500 - joinedData$full_model_predict)
  joinedData$AbsoluteDifference.750 = abs(joinedData$prediction_750 - joinedData$full_model_predict)
  joinedData$AbsoluteDifference.1000 = abs(joinedData$prediction_1000 - joinedData$full_model_predict)
  
  return(joinedData)
}

# a fucntion to make a Sythetic classification data from 2 dimensional Gaussian
makeSyData<-function(num_labeled_pos, num_unlabeled_pos, num_neg){
  SyData<-as.data.frame(mlbench.2dnormals(num_neg*2, 2, r=10, sd=3))
  SyData.positive<-sample_n(SyData[SyData['classes']==1,], size=num_labeled_pos+num_unlabeled_pos, replace = F)
  rownames(SyData.positive)<-NULL
  #unlabel 500 points
  SyData.positive[seq(num_labeled_pos+1,num_labeled_pos+num_unlabeled_pos),'classes']<-NA
  SyData.negative<-SyData[SyData['classes']==2,]
  SyData<-rbind(SyData.positive, SyData.negative)
  rownames(SyData)<-NULL
  SyData
  #plot(SyData)
}

Create updated function for synthetic data

SyPrediction <- function(trainData, ensembleSize, cmodel, kernelType, predict.mat, polynomial = FALSE) {

  positiveData = trainData[trainData$classes == 1,]
  notPositiveData = trainData[trainData$classes!=1,]
  
  #sampling from the negative data
  models <- list()
  estimated_c <- c()
  tot.acc <- c()
  
  ##Can change ensemblesize to any number based on desired number of ensembles to make
  for (r in 1:ensembleSize){
      set.seed(r)
      id <- sample(1:nrow(notPositiveData), size = length(positiveData), replace = F)
      negative.samples <- rownames(notPositiveData)[id]
      negative.train <- trainData[negative.samples, ]
  
      # classification
      x <- rbind(positiveData, negative.train)
      x <- x[,-1]
      rownames(x) <- NULL
      
      # estimating confidence
      if (cmodel == 'svm') {
      cls <- as.factor(rep(c(1, 2), times=c(nrow(positiveData), length(positiveData))))
      k <- 3
      fold <- createFolds(cls, k)
      svm_model <- svm(x[-fold$Fold1,], cls[-fold$Fold1], kernel=kernelType, probability=T, scale = F, degree = polynomial)
  
      # label 1 correspond to positive labelled examples
      p <- which(cls[fold$Fold1] == 1)
      pred <- predict(svm_model, x[fold$Fold1,][p,], decision.values=F, probability=T);
      estimated.c <- sum(attr(pred, "probabilities")[,1]) / nrow(attr(pred, "probabilities"))
      estimated_c <- c(estimated_c, estimated.c)
      
      # training base classifiers
      models[[r]] <- svm(x, cls, kernel=kernelType, probability=T, scale = F, degree = polynomial)
      }
  
      else {
      cls <- as.factor(rep(c("P", "N"), times=c(nrow(positiveData), length(positiveData))))
      k <- 3
      fold <- createFolds(cls, k)
      trnCtrl=trainControl(method='cv', number=1, returnResamp='none', summaryFunction = twoClassSummary, classProbs = TRUE)
      model=train(x[-fold$Fold1,], cls[-fold$Fold1], method=cmodel, trControl=trnCtrl,  metric = "ROC")
      
        # label p correspond to positive labelled examples
      p <- which(cls[fold$Fold1] == 'P')
        pred <- predict(object=model, x[fold$Fold1,][p,], type='prob')
        estimated.c <- sum(pred[,2]) / nrow(pred)
        estimated_c <- c(estimated_c, estimated.c)
      
    # training base classifiers
      models[[r]] <- train(x, cls, method=cmodel, trControl=trnCtrl,  metric = "ROC")  
        
      } 
    }
  
    ensemble.pred.corrected.100 <- 0
    ensemble.pred.corrected.250 <- 0
    ensemble.pred.corrected.500 <- 0
    ensemble.pred.corrected.750 <- 0
    ensemble.pred.corrected.1000 <- 0
    if (cmodel == 'svm') {
    for(i in 1:length(models)) {
        mod.pred <- predict(models[[i]], predict.mat, decision.values=TRUE, probability=TRUE)
        if (i <= 100) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.100 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.100 + attr(mod.pred,"probabilities")[,1] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        if (i <= 250) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.250 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.250 + attr(mod.pred,"probabilities")[,1] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        if (i <= 500) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.500 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.500 + attr(mod.pred,"probabilities")[,1] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        if (i <= 750) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.750 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.750 + attr(mod.pred,"probabilities")[,1] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        ensemble.pred.corrected.1000 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.1000 + attr(mod.pred,"probabilities")[,1] / estimated_c[i]
    }
    }
    else {
    for(i in 1:length(models)) {
        mod.pred <- predict(models[[i]], predict.mat, type = 'prob')
        if (i <= 100) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.100 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.100 + mod.pred[,2] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        if (i <= 250) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.250 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.250 + mod.pred[,2] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        if (i <= 500) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.500 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.500 + mod.pred[,2] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        if (i <= 750) {
            ensemble.pred.corrected.750 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.750 + mod.pred[,2] / estimated_c[i]
        }
        ensemble.pred.corrected.1000 <- ensemble.pred.corrected.1000 + mod.pred[,2] / estimated_c[i]
    }  
    }
    
    results <- list()
    predicts.100 <- (ensemble.pred.corrected.100 / 100)
    results$prediction_100 <- predicts.100/max(predicts.100)
    predicts.250 <- (ensemble.pred.corrected.250 / 250)
    results$prediction_250 <- predicts.250/max(predicts.250)
    predicts.500 <- (ensemble.pred.corrected.500 / 500)
    results$prediction_500 <- predicts.500/max(predicts.500)
    predicts.750 <- (ensemble.pred.corrected.750 / 750)
    results$prediction_750 <- predicts.750/max(predicts.750)
    predicts.1000 <- (ensemble.pred.corrected.1000 / 1000)
    results$prediction_1000 <- predicts.1000/max(predicts.1000)
    
    results$models <- models
  predictions = data.frame(results$prediction_100,results$prediction_250, results$prediction_500, results$prediction_750,     results$prediction_1000)
    
    return(predictions)
  
}

#a function to calculate the evaluation metrics
calculate_metrics<-function(SyGold, SyPred_label){
  TP=TN=FP=FN=0
  for(i in 1:length(SyGold)){
    if(SyPred_label[i]==1){
      #TP
      if(SyGold[i]==1){
        TP=TP+1}
      #FP
      if(SyGold[i]==2){
        FP=FP+1
      }
    }
    
    if(SyPred_label[i]==2){
      #TN
      if(SyGold[i]==2){
        TN=TN+1}
      #FN
      if(SyGold[i]==1){
        FN=FN+1
      }
    }
  }
  #Accuracy
  acc=(TP+TN)/(TP+TN+FP+FN)
  #Sensitivity
  se=TP/(TP+FN)
  #Specificity
  sp=TN/(FP+TN)
  #F1
  f1=2*TP/(2*TP+FP+FN)
  #GM
  GM=sqrt((TP/(TP+FN))*(TP/(TP+FP)))
  #MCC
  MCC=(TP*TN-FP*FN)/sqrt((TP+FP)*(TP+FN)*(TN+FP)*(TN+FN))
  return(c(acc, se, sp, f1, GM, MCC))
}
#evaluation metrics

Function to do AdaSampling with a Single SVM model

###A function to calculate probabilites differences
pro_diff<-function(pre_pros, this_pros){
  n=length(pre_pros)
  pd<-sum(abs(pre_pros-this_pros))/n
  return(pd)
}

###a function to do adaSampling iteration with a single SVM model
#parameters:
#LP: labeled positives
#LN: labeled negatives
#UL: unlabeled data, last(initial) prediction probabilities is stored
#pre_pros:last prediction probabilities for all the points 
require(dplyr)
adaSingleIter<-function(iter, threshold, LP, LN, UL, pre_pros){
  
  #replace positive label as 1
  LP$label<-1
  #replace negative label as 2
  LN$label<-2
  #choose negative points from ULabel probabilites
  sorted_UL<-UL[with(UL, order(pros)), ]
  negative.samples<-sorted_UL[1:20,]
  #label negative samples
  negative.samples$label<-2
  
  #prepare trainning data
  train.mat<-rbind(LP, LN, subset(negative.samples, select=-c(pros)))
  All.mat<-rbind(LP, LN, subset(UL, select=-c(pros)))
  #train a simple SVM model
  #tune the class weight due to imbalance
  svm_model <- svm(train.mat[,-1], y=as.factor(train.mat[,1]), class.weights=c('1'=2,'2'=1), probability=T, scale=F)
  #get this prediction probabilities for all instances
  pred <- predict(svm_model, All.mat[,-1], decision.values=F, probability=T)
  this_pros <- attr(pred, "probabilities")[,1]
  #add the unlabel probabilities to the data frame
  UL['pros']=attr(predict(svm_model, subset(UL, select=-c(pros))[,-1], decision.values=F, probability=T), "probabilities")[,1]
  
  #calculate probabilities difference
  pd<-pro_diff(pre_pros, this_pros)
  
  #while iter > 10000
  while(pd > threshold){
    pre_pros<-this_pros
    #choose negative points from ULabel probabilites
    sorted_UL<-UL[with(UL, order(pros)), ]
    negative.samples<-sorted_UL[1:25,]
    #label negative samples
    negative.samples$label<-2
  
    #prepare trainning data
    train.mat<-rbind(LP, LN, subset(negative.samples, select=-c(pros)))
    #train a simple SVM model
    #tune the class weight due to imbalance
    svm_model <- svm(train.mat[,-1], y=as.factor(train.mat[,1]), class.weights=c('1'=2,'2'=1), probability=T,     scale=F)
    #get this prediction probabilities for all instances
    pred <- predict(svm_model, All.mat[,-1], decision.values=F, probability=T)
    this_pros <- attr(pred, "probabilities")[,1]
    #add the unlabel probabilities to the data frame
    UL['pros']=attr(predict(svm_model, subset(UL, select=-c(pros))[,-1], decision.values=F, probability=T),      "probabilities")[,1]
  
    #calculate probabilities difference
    pd<-pro_diff(pre_pros, this_pros)
    #an iteration
    # iter=iter+1
    # print(iter)
    # print(pd)

  }
  
  #otherwise the probabilities difference reach the threshold, return UL
  #Prediction dataset
  predict.mat <- data2[,-1]
  pred <- predict(svm_model, predict.mat, decision.values=F, probability=T)
  return_pros <- data.frame(attr(pred, "probabilities")[,1])
  #print(UL['pros'])
  return(return_pros)
}


###A function to wrap adaSingleIter for initializing adaSampling
adaSampling<-function(iter, threshold, LP, LN, UL){
  #initialize the process by random sampling the negative points
  #replace positive label as 1
  LP$label<-1
  #replace negative label as 2
  LN$label<-2
  #choose negative points by random sampling
  negative.samples<-sample_n(UL, size=nrow(LP), replace=F)
  #label negative samples
  negative.samples$label<-2
  #prepare trainning data
  
  train.mat<-rbind(LP, LN, negative.samples)
  All.mat<-rbind(LP, LN, UL)
  #train a simple SVM model
  #tune the class weight due to imbalance
  svm_model <- svm(x=as.matrix(train.mat[,-1]), y=as.factor(train.mat[,1]), class.weights=c('1'=3,'2'=1),    probability=T, scale=F)
  #get this prediction probabilities for all instances
  pred <- predict(svm_model, All.mat[,-1], decision.values=F, probability=T)
  this_pros <- attr(pred, "probabilities")[,1]
  #add the unlabel probabilities to the data frame
  UL['pros']=attr(predict(svm_model, UL[,-1], decision.values=F, probability=T), "probabilities")[,1]
  predictions_result<-adaSingleIter(iter, threshold, LP, LN, UL, this_pros)
  predictions_result
  
}

Test adaSampling on Synthetic data

###A function to calculate probabilites differences
pro_diff<-function(pre_pros, this_pros){
  n=length(pre_pros)
  pd<-sum(abs(pre_pros-this_pros))/n
  return(pd)
  
}

###a function to do adaSampling on Synthetic data
require(dplyr)
SyadaSingleIter<-function(iter, threshold, LP, LN, UL, pre_pros){
  
  #replace positive label as 1
  LP['label']<-1
  #replace negative label as 2
  LN['label']<-2
  #choose negative points from ULabel probabilites
  sorted_UL<-UL[with(UL, order(pros)), ]
  #sample 20 negative points
  negative.samples<-sorted_UL[1:20,]
  
  #prepare trainning data
  train.mat<-rbind(LP, LN, subset(negative.samples, select=-c(pros)))
  All.mat<-rbind(LP, LN, subset(UL, select=-c(pros)))
  #train a simple SVM model
  #tune the class weight due to imbalance
  svm_model <- svm(train.mat[,-3], y=as.factor(train.mat[,3]), class.weights=c('1'=2,'2'=1), probability=T, scale=F)
  #get this prediction probabilities for all instances
  pred <- predict(svm_model, All.mat[,-3], decision.values=F, probability=T)
  this_pros <- attr(pred, "probabilities")[,1]
  #add the unlabel probabilities to the data frame
  UL['pros']=attr(predict(svm_model, subset(UL, select=-c(pros))[,-3], decision.values=F, probability=T), "probabilities")[,1]
  
  #calculate probabilities difference
  pd<-pro_diff(pre_pros, this_pros)
  
  #while pd > threshold
  while(pd>threshold){
    pre_pros<-this_pros
    #choose negative points from ULabel probabilites
    sorted_UL<-UL[with(UL, order(pros)), ]
    #get top 20
    negative.samples<-sorted_UL[1:20,]
    #label negative samples
    negative.samples$label<-2
  
    #prepare trainning data
    train.mat<-rbind(LP, LN, subset(negative.samples, select=-c(pros)))
    #train a simple SVM model
    #tune the class weight due to imbalance
    svm_model <- svm(train.mat[,-3], y=as.factor(train.mat[,3]), class.weights=c('1'=2,'2'=1), probability=T,     scale=F)
    #get this prediction probabilities for all instances
    pred <- predict(svm_model, All.mat[,-3], decision.values=F, probability=T)
    this_pros <- attr(pred, "probabilities")[,1]
    #add the unlabel probabilities to the data frame
    UL['pros']=attr(predict(svm_model, subset(UL, select=-c(pros))[,-3], decision.values=F, probability=T),      "probabilities")[,1]
  
    #calculate probabilities difference
    pd<-pro_diff(pre_pros, this_pros)
    #an iteration
    # iter=iter+1
    # print(iter)
    # print(pd)

  }

  return(this_pros)
}

###A function to wrap adaSingleIter for initializing adaSampling
SyadaSampling<-function(iter, threshold, LP, LN, UL){
  #initialize the process by random sampling the negative points
  #replace positive label as 1
  LP['label']<-1
  #replace negative label as 2
  LN['label']<-2
  UL['label']<-2
  #choose negative points by random sampling
  negative.samples<-sample_n(UL, size=nrow(LP), replace=F)
  #prepare trainning data
  train.mat<-rbind(LP, LN, negative.samples)
  #all the unlabel data
  All.mat<-rbind(LP, LN, UL)
  
  #train a simple SVM model
  #tune the class weight due to imbalance
  svm_model <- svm(x=as.matrix(train.mat[,-3]), y=as.factor(train.mat[,3]), class.weights=c('1'=3,'2'=1),    probability=T, scale=F)
  #get this prediction probabilities for all instances
  pred <- predict(svm_model, All.mat[,-3], decision.values=F, probability=T)
  this_pros <- attr(pred, "probabilities")[,1]
  #add the unlabel probabilities to the data frame
  UL['pros']=attr(predict(svm_model, UL[,-3], decision.values=F, probability=T), "probabilities")[,1]
  predictions_result<-SyadaSingleIter(iter, threshold, LP, LN, UL, this_pros)
  predictions_result
  
}
